tafsir[23]{c,v,t}:
  80,1,"The Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him) frowned and turned away."
  80,4,"Or that he may take heed of the advices he hears from you and benefit from them?"
  80,6,"You persevere behind them and are attentive to them."
  80,7,"What blame will there be on you if he is not purified of his sins by not repenting to Allah?"
  80,9,"And he fears his Lord."
  80,10,"You are preoccupied from him with others i.e. the senior idolaters."
  80,11,"It should not be like that; it is only admonition and a reminder for those who pay attention."
  80,15,"And they are in the hands of Messengers among the angels."
  80,17,"The disbelieving human is cursed; how severe is his disbelief in Allah!"
  80,24,"So the human who disbelieves in Allah should look at the food he eats: how did he come to acquire it?"
  80,25,"It originates from the rain descending from the sky with force and in abundance."
  80,29,"And I also make olives and date palms grow on it."
  80,30,"I also make abundant gardens and trees grow on it."
  80,33,"So when the great shriek will come that will deafen the ears i.e. the second blowing."
  80,34,"On that day a person will run from his brother."
  80,35,"And he will run from his parents."
  80,36,"And he will run from his wife and children."
  80,37,"Each one of them will be in a state where he will be preoccupied from them due to the extreme anxiety on that day."
  80,38,"The faces of the fortunate ones that day will be bright."
  80,39,"Laughing in happiness due to what Allah has prepared for them out of His mercy."
  80,40,"And the faces of the wretched people will have dust on them on that day."
  80,41,"Darkness will come over them."
  80,42,"Those described above in that state will be the ones who combined disbelief and transgression."